In order to run multiple instances of the Node, we need to use a process manager.
I highly recommend pm2 to handle process management for Node.js.


We will create 4 application server instances using PM2.

pm2 start app.js -f --3000
pm2 start app.js -f --3001
pm2 start app.js -f --3002
pm2 start app.js -f --3003


server instances will keep running in background on ports 3000, 3001, 3002, 3003
